BUILDING
========

$ ./configure
$ make
$ su -c "make install"

RUNNING
=======

$ releasetracker moviefile
$ cat moviefile
movie 1
movie 2
movie 3
movie 4

Put in cron job and run every once in a while, and you'll wake up with a mail
listing to all the new movies you want to pirate.

The movie file argument can be a relative path, an absolute path, or an URI
using any protocol GIO supports.

